  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\nbug\r\n\r\n**What is the current behavior?**\r\npasting this string \"12/11/2013\" into either of the 2 input fields, one of type date and the other text\r\n```\r\n<input type=\"text\" id=\"1\" onPaste={e => console.log(e.target, e.clipboardData.getData('text'))}/>\r\n<input type=\"date\" id=\"2\" onPaste={e => console.log(e.target, e.clipboardData.getData('text'))}/>\r\n```\r\nresult from console:\r\n```\r\n<input type=\"text\" id=\"1\"> \"12/11/2013\" // when pasting into the date input\r\n<input type=\"text\" id=\"1\"> \"12/11/2013\"  // when pasting into the text input\r\n```\r\nwhen pasting into either input, the event.target is the input[type=text]\r\n\r\n**What is the expected behavior?**\r\nevent target should be input type date when pasting into the date input and likewise for type text\r\n```\r\n<input type=\"text\" id=\"1\"> \"12/11/2013\"\r\n<input type=\"date\" id=\"2\"> \"12/11/2013\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Which versions of React, and which browser / OS are affected by this issue? Did this work in previous versions of React?**\r\n```\r\n\"react\": \"^16.2.0\",\r\n\"react-dom\": \"^16.2.0\",\r\n```\r\nChrome: Version 63.0.3239.132 (Official Build) (64-bit)\r\n\r\nFor Firefox 57.0.1\r\nthe paste event does not trigger on the input[type=date] at all",
